      type: "Vasopressin Analogue (Splanchnic Vasoconstrictor)",
      action: "Selectively constricts splanchnic arterial vasculature via V1 receptor activation, increasing effective arterial blood volume and improving renal perfusion; combined with albumin for volume expansion",
      sideEffects: "Ischemic complications (coronary, mesenteric, peripheral — most serious), abdominal cramping, diarrhea, bradycardia, hyponatremia",
